# üåø SDF ‚Äì Final Portfolio Piece

This project is my final portfolio piece for Software Development Fundamentals.   
It is built using **HTML5 and CSS3**, and is a faithful implementation of a provided Figma design.

The goal of the project was to accurately recreate the layout, spacing, colours, typography, and component structure seen in the Figma file while keeping the site responsive and professionally coded.

---

## üé® Figma Reference  
All sizes, colours, spacing, grid layouts and typography were taken directly from the official Figma design:

üîó https://www.figma.com/design/fM2tutgIH0k1SrNir4MVe3/SDF-Resume-Project-STUDENT-REFERENCE-FILE?node-id=0-1

---

## üß† What This Project Includes (Based on My HTML Structure)

### ‚úÖ **1. Profile Section**
- Profile image sized exactly using **280‚Äì300px responsive aspect-ratio**
- Name and personal bio
- Fully responsive layout using grid + flexible width values  
- Grey dotted background using **CSS radial gradient**

### ‚úÖ **2. Proficiency Section**
- Semantic structure using `<section>` and `<div>`
- Green progress bars with exact height, colour, and spacing
- Labels: Beginner, Intermediate, Advanced
- Uses Figma-matching font sizes (19.36px) and correct spacing

### ‚úÖ **3. Skills Section**
- Skills displayed as mint-green tags  
- Responsive wrapping using `flex-wrap`
- Styled according to Figma (rounded tags, bold text)

### ‚úÖ **4. Projects Section**
- White background for the main Projects container  
- 4 project cards using CSS Grid  
- First card styled as **dark green (featured)**  
- All other cards = **mint green**  
- **Red heart icons** restored and styled without background borders  
- Uses `auto-fit` grid for fully responsive behaviour

### ‚úÖ **5. Education Section**
- First item (‚ÄúCodeSpace Academy‚Äù) styled in **dark green** to match Figma  
- All other items styled in mint  
- Semantic structure using cards + bullet lists  
- Left/right layout using two-column flexible grid

### ‚úÖ **6. Tools Section**
- Organised into 3 categories: Languages, Design, Tools  
- Uses Devicons (HTML, CSS, Node.js, Tailwind, Figma, Google, Git, GitHub)
- Column layout for mobile, vertical stacking for desktop

### ‚úÖ **7. Experience Section**
- Featured experience box (Absa ) highlighted in dark green  (Mostrecent)
- Badge ‚ÄúMost Recent‚Äù included  
- Other experience cards styled mint green  
- Clean two-column layout  
- Uses semantic HTML + bullet lists  

### ‚úÖ **8. Footer**
- Orange footer (#D86A45)
- Email, LinkedIn, GitHub links in **white text (as required)**
- Flexbox layout for spacing

---

## üß© Responsive Design Techniques Used (Based on My CSS)

This project includes custom responsiveness using:

### ‚úî **CSS Grid with minmax()**
Used in:
- Profile section  
- Top-grid  
- Projects grid  
- Bottom-grid  
- Education + Experience sections  

### ‚úî **auto-fit / auto-fill grids**
Used to make Projects section fully responsive without breaking layout.

### ‚úî **flex-wrap**
Used for skills tags, tools section, footer, etc.



